hotBrief
Copyright 2026 hotBrief contributors

This product includes software developed by third parties, listed below.

================================================================================
DailyHotApi
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A self-hosted hot-list aggregation API for 30+ Chinese platforms.
Source: https://github.com/imsyy/DailyHotApi
License: MIT

hotBrief consumes the DailyHotApi HTTP interface as an upstream data source.
The DailyHotApi project itself is not bundled or modified; it is run as a
separate Docker container.

================================================================================
Jina Reader (r.jina.ai)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A free, hosted readability service that converts arbitrary URLs into clean
Markdown. Used by hotBrief's fulltext lane to fetch article bodies.
Source: https://github.com/jina-ai/reader
License: Apache License 2.0

hotBrief calls the public r.jina.ai endpoint as a third-party HTTP service;
no source code is bundled.

================================================================================
ServerChan (Server酱)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A WeChat push notification gateway service.
Service: https://sct.ftqq.com

hotBrief calls the ServerChan HTTPS API as a third-party push channel.

